<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05020f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05020f">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05020f"> 20(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> posca (wine &amp; vinegar)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">According to John, Jesus cried out on the cross, &ldquo;I thirst,&rdquo; and the soldiers gave him vinegar &mdash; perhaps the <mark><i>posca</i>, or vinegar and water</mark>, served out to the Roman army. This would be an act of humanity, yet Luke has the foolish impudence to say it was done in mockery. <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [The Crucifixion] 200</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
